{% comment %}
  Shared template for Google Photos plugin
  This file contains reusable assets and variables for all layout templates:
  - Google Photos icon (base64-encoded) for title bars
  - Photo selection logic (currently handled by backend API)
{% endcomment %}

{% comment %}
  Google Photos icon for title bars (59x59px, base64-encoded PNG)
  Usage in templates:
    <img src="{{ icon_google_photos }}" class="icon" alt="Google Photos">
  
  This icon is a stylized version of the Google Photos logo optimized for e-ink displays:
  - 59x59px resolution (optimal for TRMNL title bars)
  - PNG format with transparency
  - Base64-encoded for direct embedding
{% endcomment %}
{%- capture icon_google_photos -%}
data:image/png;base64,
{%- endcapture -%}

{% comment %}
  Photo data is provided by the backend API endpoint (/api/photo)
  The following variables are available from the JSON response:
  
  - photo_url: Optimized full-resolution photo URL (1040×780 for TRMNL X)
  - thumbnail_url: Lower resolution version (400×300, optional)
  - caption: Photo caption/description (may be empty)
  - timestamp: When photo was taken/updated (ISO 8601 format)
  - album_name: Name of the source album
  - photo_count: Total number of photos in album
{% endcomment %}

{% comment %}
  ====================================================================================
  REUSABLE LIQUID TEMPLATES
  ====================================================================================
  These templates follow TRMNL best practices for DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) code.
  Reference: https://docs.usetrmnl.com/go/reusing-markup
{% endcomment %}

{% comment %}
  Photo Display Template
  ----------------------
  Renders a photo with optimal settings for e-ink displays.
  
  Parameters:
  - photo_url: URL of the photo to display (required)
  - caption: Alt text for accessibility (optional)
  
  Usage:
    {% render "photo_display", photo_url: photo_url, caption: caption %}
{% endcomment %}
{% template photo_display %}
<!-- Custom max-width/max-height ensures images fit without cut-off (handles portrait/landscape/any aspect ratio) -->
<img src="{{ photo_url }}" 
     alt="{{ caption }}" 
     class="image image--contain image-dither"
     style="max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%; object-fit: contain;">
{% endtemplate %}
